---
title: One-Pan Pork & Pineapple Tacos with Pickled Veggies & Lemon Crema
description: We’re obsessed with sweet and savory flavor combos for dinner, which is why we have a soft spot for tacos al pastor. The dish traditionally involves pork that’s marinated in pineapple juice and spices, then slowly spit-roasted for ultra-tender results. In this riff on the classic, we skip the hours of slow-cooking by swapping out the pork shoulder for ground pork. It’s browned with a bounty of Southwest spices, simmered with chunks of pineapple until saucy, and stuffed into warm tortillas with lemon crema and pickled onion and radish. You can have all that in just 30 minutes—taco ’bout a dinner winner!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-pork-pineapple-tacos-828c38c5.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-pork-pineapple-tacos-61ddde8430ed832e5a66577d-04abde00.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-pork-and-pineapple-tacos-61ddde8430ed832e5a66577d
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
